          <h1>Beginner's Training Program: Kickstart Your Fitness Journey</h1>

          <p>Welcome to our gym community! Whether you're a fitness enthusiast or someone who's just starting their fitness journey, this beginner's training program is designed to help you build a strong foundation. Remember, consistency is key, and progress is a gradual process.</p>
      
          <h2>Warm-up Routine:</h2>
      
          <p>Before diving into the workout, it's crucial to prepare your body. A proper warm-up increases blood flow to your muscles and helps prevent injuries. Spend 5-10 minutes doing light cardio exercises such as jumping jacks or jogging in place.</p>
      
          <h2>Day 1: Full Body Strength</h2>
      
          <h3>Exercise 1: Bodyweight Squats</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Sets: 3</li>
              <li>Reps: 10-12</li>
              <li>Description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. Keep your chest up and back straight.</li>
          </ul>
      
          <h3>Exercise 2: Push-ups</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Sets: 3</li>
              <li>Reps: 8-10</li>
              <li>Description: Assume a plank position, lower your body towards the ground, and push back up. Modify by performing knee push-ups if needed.</li>
          </ul>
      
          <h3>Exercise 3: Bent-Over Rows</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Sets: 3</li>
              <li>Reps: 10</li>
              <li>Description: Hold dumbbells or household objects, hinge at the hips, and pull the weights towards your chest, keeping your back straight.</li>
          </ul>
      
          <h3>Exercise 4: Plank</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Sets: 3</li>
              <li>Duration: 20-30 seconds</li>
              <li>Description: Maintain a plank position, engaging your core and keeping a straight line from head to heels.</li>
          </ul>
      
          <h2>Day 2: Cardiovascular Training</h2>
      
          <h3>Cardio Workout:</h3>
          <ul>
              <li>Activity: Brisk walking or jogging</li>
              <li>Duration: 20-30 minutes</li>
              <li>Additional: Include 10 minutes of jump rope if possible.</li>
          </ul>
      
          <h2>Conclusion:</h2>
      
          <p>Consistency and dedication will help you achieve your fitness goals. Remember to listen to your body, stay hydrated, and maintain a balanced diet. Feel free to adjust the intensity based on your fitness level, and always consult with a fitness professional if you have any concerns.</p>
      
          <p>Stay motivated and enjoy your fitness journey with us!</p>
          </article>
        <article id="intermediate">
            <h2>Intermediate Training Program: Elevate Your Fitness Levels</h2>
            <p>Congratulations on reaching the intermediate level! This program is designed to elevate your fitness levels with a combination of strength training and cardiovascular exercises. Here's a sample workout routine:</p>

            <h3>Day 1: Strength and Endurance</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Weighted Squats: 4 sets of 8-10 reps</li>
                <li>Push-ups with Rotation: 3 sets of 12 reps</li>
                <li>Dumbbell Rows: 3 sets of 12 reps per arm</li>
                <li>Plank with Shoulder Taps: 3 sets, 30 seconds each</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Day 2: High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Jump Squats: 4 sets of 20 seconds</li>
                <li>Mountain Climbers: 3 sets of 30 seconds</li>
                <li>Box Jumps: 3 sets of 12 reps</li>
                <li>Rest: 1 minute between sets</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Challenge yourself, but listen to your body. Ensure proper form during exercises and consider increasing weights gradually.</p>
        </article>

